source_jobs.description:
Hi there! We’re CyberCare - part of Tesonet Accelerator - a customer care company for global tech brands. We combine AI-powered automation with a human touch to create smooth, stress-free experiences for millions of technology users worldwide. With 450+ professionals on board, we make the tech-world easy - one customer at a time.



We are looking for a Talent Acquisition specialist for a fixed-term contract with a possibility to transition into a permanent position.



A strong match for this role is someone who



 - Has some experience in recruiting, sourcing, or a similar role - just enough to feel comfortable getting started without learning everything from zero;

 - Is comfortable working at a fast pace and managing several searches at once;

 - Is detail-oriented and genuinely tech-savvy - you pick up new tools quickly (Ashby, Canditech);

 - Is data-minded: comfortable working with recruitment metrics such as fill rate, interview-to-offer rate, time-to-hire, and time-to-fill;

 - Is results-driven, but a team player first - we've built a strong, collaborative culture and want to keep it that way;

 - Is fluent in English, both spoken and written;

 - Is available to work full-time.

 

What You’ll Do and Learn

 

 - Run high-volume, entry-level recruitment, primarily for Customer Support roles;

 - Step in as back-up on other types of searches when needed (e.g. tech, back office roles);

 - Source and screen candidates across multiple channels: job boards, referrals, social media, and professional networks;

 - Organize and conduct interviews, and support our hiring managers in running theirs;

 - Work closely with our ATS (Ashby) - and help us tidy up, structure, and automate our workflows;

 - Create a great candidate experience at every stage of the process;

 - Track and use recruitment data to spot what's working and what can be improved.



The Perks of Joining Us

 - Smooth start in tech with onboarding & mentorship.

 - Office in a great location + option to work from home twice a week (after probation period).

 - Health insurance, free in-house 24/7 gym & workout sessions.

 - Kitchen full of snacks & bakery goods on Fridays.

 - Various internal and online training, books - everything you need to reach your full potential.

 - Clear growth path - move inside of CyberCare or Tesonet.

 

Compensation and contract:

 - Gross Salary 1850 - 2200 EUR/month;

 - The role starts as a 6-month fixed-term contract, with the potential to transition into a permanent position.
